Write a FOCUSED article of about 350-400 words on the topic implied by the SEARCH RESULTS below. Keep it COMPACT (well under 3500 characters total including sources). RULES: (1) Ground EVERY factual claim, statistic, date, and quote ONLY in the SEARCH RESULTS. (2) After each sourced claim add an inline marker like [1], [2] matching the numbered source. (3) End with a '## Sources' section. The SEARCH RESULTS already contain a '## Sources' list - COPY those source lines EXACTLY as written (same titles, same URLs), do NOT invent, alter, shorten, reorder, or add ANY URL, and only use [n] numbers that exist in that list. If you are unsure a URL is in the list, leave it out. (4) If the results are thin or off-topic, say so plainly instead of padding. (5) No hype words (revolutionary, game-changing, seamless, cutting-edge). Plain ASCII only.

SEARCH RESULTS:
{{INPUT}}

Audit the research article below for FABRICATION and grounding only. NOTE: the text may be cut off at the end for length (a '[... truncated ...]' note); if so, judge only the complete content before it and do NOT fail because the final source entry is cut off. IT IS FINE if the article does not cite every source, and citation numbers may be non-sequential or skip values (e.g. [1][2][5]) - do NOT fail for skipped, missing, or out-of-order [n] numbers; that is normal. FAIL ONLY if ANY of: (A) a cited claim's number has NO matching entry in the '## Sources' list; (B) a statistic, date, named figure, or quote is clearly fabricated (not attributable to any listed source); (C) there is NO '## Sources' section, or it has fewer than 2 entries with real-looking http(s) URLs; (D) a Sources URL is obviously fabricated gibberish (random/unreadable domain); (E) the article is hype-only filler with no substance; (F) it contains non-ASCII characters. If none of A-F apply, reply with exactly the single word: VALID. Otherwise reply with exactly: PIPELINE_VALIDATION_FAILED: <one short reason>. Output nothing else.

